{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This family consists of several ROS/MUCR transcriptional regulator proteins. The ros chromosomal gene is present in octopine and nopaline strains of Agrobacterium tumefaciens as well as in Rhizobium meliloti (Sinorhizobium meliloti). This gene encodes a 15.5kDa protein that specifically represses the virC and virD operons in the virulence region of the Ti plasmid [[cite:PUB00011445]] and is necessary for succinoglycan production [[cite:PUB00011446]]. S. meliloti can produce two types of acidic exopolysaccharides, succinoglycan and galactoglucan, that are interchangeable for infection of Medicago sativa (Alfalfa) nodules. MucR from S. meliloti acts as a transcriptional repressor that blocks the expression of the exp genes responsible for galactoglucan production therefore allowing the exclusive production of succinoglycan [[cite:PUB00011447]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR041920", "name" "ROS/MUCR transcriptional regulator superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF05443" "ROS/MUCR transcriptional regulator protein"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "ROS/MUCR transcriptional regulator", "short" "ROS_MUCR"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 1, "domain_architectures" 31, "proteomes" 1249, "taxa" 4693, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 10166, "sets" 0, "proteins" 10154, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 8431}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR008807", :literature {"PUB00011445" {"URL" nil, "issue" "8", "authors" ["Cooley MB" "D'Souza MR" "Kado CI."], "ISO_journal" "J. Bacteriol.", "DOI_URL" "http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/picrender.fcgi?tool=EBI&pubmedid=2013576&action=stream&blobtype=pdf", "medline_journal" "J Bacteriol", "title" "The virC and virD operons of the Ag